parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially when the vehicle surges forward unexpectedly.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without input from the driver
the vehicle surges forward
the brakes fail to slow or stop the vehicle
the vehicle takes off unexpectedly
the vehicle crashes into objects or other vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front lower ball joint can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or injuries. It can also lead to premature wear on other suspension components.
symptoms: Loud squeaking noise from the front lower ball joint
failure of the front lower ball joint
clunking noise when going over speed bumps
vibration in the seats
shuddering of the steering wheel at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the traction control system can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or injuries, especially on slippery roads.
symptoms: Vehicle fishtails to one side
loss of traction
difficulty controlling the vehicle on snow-covered roads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The suspension vibration can cause discomfort to the driver and passengers, and may lead to premature wear on other suspension components.
symptoms: Vibration in the seats
shuddering of the steering wheel at high speeds
clunking noise when going over speed bumps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while driving, leading to a loss of power steering and potentially causing accidents, especially when entering heavy traffic or freeways.
symptoms: The engine suddenly turns off while driving
the vehicle cuts off while accelerating
the headlights flicker
the battery drains
and the alternator is damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the battery to drain, leading to electrical system failures, stalling, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The battery drains
the alternator is damaged
and the electrical system fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel system leak can cause gas leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Gas leaks from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Pedal Misapplication Due to Design Flaw
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the accelerator and brake pedals can cause the driver's foot to accidentally engage the accelerator pedal while applying the brake, leading to unintended acceleration and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks forward while applying the brake pedal
sudden acceleration while attempting to stop
near-miss accidents or collisions due to unintended acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine dies or stalls while driving
resulting in a loss of power
causing the vehicle to come to a sudden stop or lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents, injuries, or being stranded on the road.
symptoms: The engine dies or stalls while driving
resulting in a loss of power
causing the vehicle to come to a sudden stop or lose control.
